\taxon{Problem}
\title{Monotonicity is insufficient}
\p{Consider this [monotonic](dt-000J) function #{g} defined over a [cpo](dt-001D) #{(\mathbb{R} \cup \{\infty,-\infty\}, \leq)}:
##{g(x) = \begin{cases}
				\tan^{-1} x & \text{if}\ x < 0\\
				1 & \text{otherwise}
			  \end{cases}
 }
 Note this function is not continuous at 0. Starting from our [#{\bot} element](dt-000A) #{-\infty}, we can see that the limit of the [ascending Kleene chain](dt-000X) is #{0}:
 ##{
 \begin{array}{lcl}
 g(-\infty) & = & -\frac{\pi}{2}\\
 g(-\frac{\pi}{2}) & = & -1\\
 g(-1) & \approx & -0.78\\	
 \end{array}
 }
 But #{g(0) = 1}! â€” the [lub](dt-0017) of the [Kleene chain](dt-000X) is \em{not} a [fixed point](dt-000S)! 
}
